    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-30T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-30T08:00:00-05:00" n="1109"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1109">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Italy)/7–3045: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1109<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Assistant to the President’s Personal Representative at
                        Vatican City</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_THHJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tittmann</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1109fn1">The gist of this message was included in telegram
                        No. 169 of July 31 from <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">Grew</persName> to
                            <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName> (file No. 800.00
                        Summaries/7–3145).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vatican City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-30T15:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 30, 1945—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>180. My 155, June 26.<note n="2" xml:id="d1109fn2">Not printed.</note> Brigadier
                        <persName corresp="#p_HMGEE1">General Hume</persName>[,] Sr Civil Affairs
                    officer Allied Military Govt, after audience with <persName corresp="#p_P1"
                        >Pope</persName> July 28, reports burden of <persName corresp="#p_P1"
                        >Pope</persName>’s conversation was his concern lest Allied troops be
                    withdrawn from Italy before conditions become normal again. <persName
                        corresp="#p_HMGEE1">Gen Hume</persName> said other highly placed
                    ecclesiastics of his acquaintance in Rome including two Cardinals took occasion
                    of his presence here now to speak emphatically to him in similar vein.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_THHJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tittmann</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
